		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;07/12/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 20:21:03</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=7102"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
        
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=7102')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=48913&amp;TOPIC_ID=5986&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=dueling+question&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I feel extremely compelled to answer this question since it happens to be asked a lot.  </P><P>I duel a lot.  I find practice makes you better at it and I just enjoy the challenge, so here is the info on exp loss.</P><P>Long ago, yes, a dot would result in exp lost, but many patches ago this was corrected.  Pets no longer take exp either.  I have tested this on many "volunteers" over and over, and I have also tested it on a seperate account dueling one of my own characters.</P><P>Your dueling opponent will STILL LOSE EXP int the following situation:</P><P>If he dies to a dot or pet while you have him feared, and not one of your nukes he or she will lose exp.  The reason is because the player is in a LD/NPC mode at that time, so will exp death just as a LD kill would be.</P><P>Gladly, I rarely have this problem because of the way I have found is most effective in duels.  Never fear your opponent, simply shadowstep and fight as you normally would without fearing.</P><P>My duel approach against most classes, is as follows:</P><P>Begin the fight with any pet you like, pets don't hit PCs very well, so it's merely a distraction ;).  The player is likely to come running straight for you, shadowstep.  Find your opponent and within spell casting range put  Vexing Mordinia or Bond of Death on them.  I then shadowstep again.  Find opponent again, who by now is getting backstabed by my rogue pet, and apply splurt.  Shadowstep, change robes.  Dressed in your new different looking robe, lifetap, I like deflux for the speed.  Shadowstep, change robes.  </P><P>Never try to root.  Never try using anything except irresistable spells.  </P><P>I have found this method never causes exp loss, I rarely loose a duel, and my record was a cocky bard that died in under 30 secs.</P><P>Good luck, hope this helps answer your question.</P><P></P><P></P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

